@NODE REQUIRED "What you need to run Wolf3D"
@SMARTWRAP
@{b}Requirements@{ub}


You'll need the following to be able to start Wolf3D:@{LINE}


·@{LINDENT 2} 68020+ (68040+ recommended)
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} AGA, CyberGraphX or Picasso96
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} AmigaOS 3.0
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} about 8MB FastRAM
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} dmxemul.library
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} PC Wolf3D V1.4 shareware files
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}


That's it.@{LINE}

@ENDNODE
@NODE FEATURES "What you can do with it"
@SMARTWRAP
@{b}Features@{ub}


The current features include:


·@{LINDENT 2} Fully multitasks
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} Support for AGA/CyberGraphX/Picasso96 direct video access
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} Support for different screen modes
