@ENDNODE
@NODE INSTALL "How to install and use"
@SMARTWRAP
@{b}Installation@{ub}


Get the PC Wolf3D V1.4 shareware files and copy them into your Wolf3D drawer.
Delete any remaining config.#? files as they are incompatible with the Amiga version!

That's all - fairly simple, isn't it?

@ENDNODE
@NODE USAGE "How to use Wolf3D"
@SMARTWRAP
@{b}Usage@{ub}


Wolf3D can be started via Icon from Workbench or from Shell.@{LINE}
Make sure, that the stack is set large enough, as I haven't compiled in any stack extension code.
An amount of 60KB should be large enough (if the game crashes, try to increase the stack).@{LINE}


The currently supported commandline/tooltype arguments are:@{LINE}

@{b}-fpu@{ub}@{LINDENT 26}                      Enable FPU routines
You should use that switch on a 68060 with FPU
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
@{b}-mmu@{ub}@{LINDENT 26}                      Enable MMU hack
Needs a 040/060 with working MMU
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
@{b}-smgame <screenmode>@{ub}@{LINDENT 26}      Screenmode to use for the game
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
@{b}-directgfx@{ub}@{LINDENT 26}                Make use of direct accessing the videomem on a
AGA/CyberGraphX/Picasso96 screen.
If not enabled, WritePixel#?() will be used
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
@{b}-nodoublebuffer@{ub}@{LINDENT 26}           Disables doublebuffering
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
@{b}-fps@{ub}@{LINDENT 26}                      Enables a frame counter in the upper left corner
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}

@ENDNODE
@NODE HISTORY "What has changed"
@SMARTWRAP
@{b}History@{ub}


@{i}The following text is from the original readme by Sebastian:@{ui}


 I have started porting this game in summer 1998. But I gave up after
a week, because the sources was a big mess. Couple of days ago, I have
found a Linux port (made by Steven Fuller <relnev@atdot.org>, and can be found at
http://jcs.jsteintech.com/wolf3d/), which was far better than the Id sources
(all the crapy 16 bit Borland C references was removed ;) And I started again.@{LINE}
This is what I get after two sleepless nights.


v0.15@{LINE}
        - I have added too much swaping routines last time ;)@{LINE}
          Sprites graphics was screwed. Fixed.@{LINE}
        - It also seems that I have fixed the 'palette shifting bug'.@{LINE}
          Belive me, it was not me! It just started to work.@{LINE}
        - much faster (11fps full screen on 040/25)@{LINE}

v0.1@{LINE}
        - added a lot of byte swaping routines, which fixes almost@{LINE}
          all known bugs. All menu options are working now.@{LINE}
        - Saveing & loading game now works.@{LINE}
        - Added faster drawing routines.@{LINE}
        - still only Wolfenstein3D demo files works with this release.@{LINE}

v0.01   (initial release)@{LINE}
        - just compiled the source.@{LINE}
        - There is a lot of limitations:@{LINE}
           1) it is only working with Wolf3D demo data files@{LINE}
              (ftp://ftp.gamers.org/pub/games/wolf3d/official/1wolf14.zip)@{LINE}
              THOSE FILES MUST BE INSTALLED ON pEEcEE FIRST!!!@{LINE}
              Version for registereed data, and also for 'Spear of Destiny'@{LINE}
              soon. This will be different executables for every version@{LINE}
              of data or (if I get enough time) one executable.@{LINE}
           2) Game can crash in any moment. Also some of the menu options@{LINE}
              does not works (like 'read this' in main menu).@{LINE}
        - It is not as fast as I expected. Some additional optimizations@{LINE}
          are still required.@{LINE}
        - no sound at all.@{LINE}
        - save game does not work. (or maybe does? loading@{LINE}
                                    does not work for sure ;)@{LINE}
        - Only keyboard control works. Mouse & Joystick is not supported.


@{i}Now that's what I (Christian) have done:@{ui}


I also started a port some time ago, but stopped working on it as the original sources
by Id were just too bad...


0.16 - 0.18     06-Apr-99


·@{LINDENT 2} merged Sebastian's Wolf3D sources with mine
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} recompiled with EGCS 1.1.2
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} added screenmode requester and integrated the c2p stuff
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} timing is done with dmxemul.library now
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} options may be specified as tooltypes
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} delays via VBL are more exact now
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} added two nice icons by Andreas Kürzinger and Raymond Cruz
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} I'm sure that I've forgotten something... :)
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}

0.19 - 0.20     17-Dec-03


·@{LINDENT 2} Picasso96 is now only used when its main task is running
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} linked with libnix 2.0
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} MMU hack now needs mmu.library (and isn't that hacky anymore ;))
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} reworked multi-line strings in extended asm
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} recompiled with gcc 3.3.0
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}
·@{LINDENT 2} created a new GlowIcon set (using the original 32 color palette)
@{LINDENT 0}@{PAR}

0.21		13-Aug-04


